modules.description: Provides functions to define and run unit tests, assert conditions, and generate colored output and JUnit-compatible reports. Works with test cases, test suites, and assertions involving values, exceptions, and side effects. Used to validate individual functions, check error handling, and integrate testing into build processes.

Wraps Lwt-based functions for use in OUnit tests, enabling asynchronous test execution. Accepts functions that return Lwt values and integrates them into test cases. Used to validate asynchronous operations like network requests or delayed computations within test suites.
